
TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Effects of Goal Setting, External Feedback, and Self-Generated Feedback on Outcome Variables: A Field Experiment
AU  - Ivancevich, John M.
AU  - McMahon, J. Timothy
Y1  - 1982/06/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255997
DO  - 10.5465/255997
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 359
EP  - 372
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study compared the motivational impact of goal setting and performance feedback on four measures of performance, intrinsic and extrinsic satisfaction, and organizational commitment. Goal setting was found to be superior to nongoal-setting, feedback was superior to nonfeedback, and self-generated feedback with goal setting was more powerful than externally generated feedback with goal setting.
AB  - This study compared the motivational impact of goal setting and performance feedback on four measures of performance, intrinsic and extrinsic satisfaction, and organizational commitment. Goal setting was found to be superior to nongoal-setting, feedback was superior to nonfeedback, and self-generated feedback with goal setting was more powerful than externally generated feedback with goal setting.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255997
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255997
Y2  - 2026/04/24
