TY  - JOUR
T1  - Interorganizational Linkages and Influence Over Decision Making
AU  - Provan, Keith G.
Y1  - 1982/06/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256003
DO  - 10.5465/256003
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 443
EP  - 451
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article examines the linkages between 46 human service agencies and their local United Way organization to determine the extent to which an agency's dependence on United Way for scarce resources as well as its linkages to other resource suppliers is related to United Way influence over agency decision making. It is prevalent among human service agencies to establish formal relations with a resource supplier as a means of reducing uncertainty. The reason for an agency to affiliate formally with United Way is the capacity of United Way to reduce uncertainty regarding the acquisition of funding.
AB  - The article examines the linkages between 46 human service agencies and their local United Way organization to determine the extent to which an agency's dependence on United Way for scarce resources as well as its linkages to other resource suppliers is related to United Way influence over agency decision making. It is prevalent among human service agencies to establish formal relations with a resource supplier as a means of reducing uncertainty. The reason for an agency to affiliate formally with United Way is the capacity of United Way to reduce uncertainty regarding the acquisition of funding.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256003
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256003
Y2  - 2026/04/24
