T1  - The Measurement of Firm Diversification: Some New Empirical Evidence
AU  - Montgomery, Cynthia A.
Y1  - 1982/06/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255992
DO  - 10.5465/255992
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 299
EP  - 307
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Two approaches to the measurement of firm diversification are compared: (1) continuous SIC-based product count measures and (2) categorical measures as popularized by Rumelt. The measures are found to be more similar than previous research has suggested, although each appears to have advantages for particular research topics and methodological approaches.
AB  - Two approaches to the measurement of firm diversification are compared: (1) continuous SIC-based product count measures and (2) categorical measures as popularized by Rumelt. The measures are found to be more similar than previous research has suggested, although each appears to have advantages for particular research topics and methodological approaches.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255992
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255992
