T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 237
EP  - 253
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In a Canadian study the locus of control of top executives was found to bear a direct and significant relationship to the nature of corporate strategy but an indirect relationship to environment and to structure. More internal chief executives tended to pursue more product-market innovation, undertake greater risks, and lead rather than follow competitors.
AB  - In a Canadian study the locus of control of top executives was found to bear a direct and significant relationship to the nature of corporate strategy but an indirect relationship to environment and to structure. More internal chief executives tended to pursue more product-market innovation, undertake greater risks, and lead rather than follow competitors.
