N2  - The results of a study of the ethics of publishing and reviewing research indicated (1) substantial dissensus about whether standards exist; (2) vague or nonexistent mechanisms for communicating standards; and (3) few institutionalized penalties for violating ethical standards. Implications for organizational behavior as a developing profession are raised.
