N2  - This study evaluated the effectiveness of an intervention package (feedback, competition, and incentives) in reducing the accident rate of urban transit operators. Results showed a 24.9 percent reduction in accident rates, establishing a definite link between the intervention and reduction in accident rates, severity, and cost.
